article.description: — Jamaree Bouyea had 22 points as San Francisco won its ninth straight home game, routing Loyola Marymount 97-73 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Bouyea lifts San Francisco over Loyola Marymount 97-73
article.linkText: Bouyea lifts San Francisco over Loyola Marymount 97-73
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- — Jamaree Bouyea had 22 points as San Francisco won its ninth straight home game, routing Loyola Marymount 97-73 on Thursday night. Khalil Shabazz had 17 points and six assists for San Francisco (15-2, 2-0 West Coast Conference). Zane Meeks added 14 points. Yauhen Massalski had 13 points and eight rebounds. The Dons forced a season-high 21 turnovers. Eli Scott had 22 points for the Lions (7-6, 0-1). Dameane Douglas added 15 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
